    q: 'Why do so many Laveen homes have AC problems in their first few summers?',
    a: 'Laveen has been one of Phoenix\'s fastest-growing residential areas, and rapid growth means rapid construction. Builders install HVAC systems to meet minimum code requirements — sized to pass inspection, not to handle the actual thermal load of your specific home on a 115°F afternoon with full occupancy. Many Laveen homeowners discover in their second or third summer that the system runs constantly but can\'t hold the thermostat setting. John Rigo can diagnose what is actually happening and give you a straight answer.'
